<TITLE> Govt deploys video piracy busters </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 02 (bdnews24.com) A taskforce, headed by a RAB deputy director, has been formed to stop video piracy and the making and screening of obscene films, the government said in a statement Tuesday. The deputy director (intelligence) of RAB Headquarters has been appointed as the convener of the taskforce. According to the statement, the taskforce is empowered to seize obscene posters and prints and hand over the suspects to law enforcers. The taskforce will also be able to take steps against cinema halls that screened movies with obscene content. The taskforce is empowered to arrest people involved in video piracy. bdnews2
